## Additional Permissions for Educational Use

This software is specifically designed for educational purposes within the 42 School
ecosystem. Students and educators are granted additional permissions to:

1. Use this software in academic projects and assignments
2. Modify and adapt the code for learning purposes
3. Share modifications within the 42 School community
4. Use in portfolios and project demonstrations

## Attribution

When using this software in academic or professional contexts, please provide
appropriate attribution:

"AST Visualizer by Pedro Gomes (@pgomes42) - https://github.com/pgomes42/visualize_ar"

## 42 School Specific Terms

This project was developed as part of the 42 School curriculum. It is intended
to help students understand and visualize Abstract Syntax Trees in their
Minishell implementations.

For questions regarding usage in 42 School projects, please consult with your
curriculum staff or refer to your school's academic integrity policies.